Day 18: Nested Routes in React Router

Nested Routes allow you to create parent-child routes.

Example:

/dashboard
/dashboard/profile
/dashboard/settings
/dashboard/users

Instead of creating separate pages, you can have a common Dashboard layout and load child pages inside it.

Why Nested Routes?

Suppose every Dashboard page should show:

Dashboard Header
Dashboard Menu

Profile Page

or

Dashboard Header
Dashboard Menu

Settings Page

Without nested routes, you would repeat the header and menu in every component.

Nested routes solve this problem.

